review:
Sorry for the the original tag line but it's so so soooo true!<br/><br/>Pros;
<ul><li>The casting of Chris Pratt as Emmet Brickowski is so great! He gives the character a real sense of goofiness whilst making them likeable instead of mind numbingly irritating.</li><li>Elizabeth Banks, Morgan Freeman, Will Arnet, Alison Brie, Nick Offerman, Charlie Day &amp; Liam Neeson as Wyldestyle, Vitruvius, Batman, Unikitty, Metalbeard, Benny &amp; Good/Bad/Scribble-Face Cop are all spectacular and bring their own laughs and even emotion to their supporting characters.</li><li>You know Will Ferrel? The guy who you hire when you spent all of your budget in a crappy script? Well here he is and he is actually really good! His villain Lord Business is really entertaining yet you can understand what he represents.</li><li>The animation is so unique and whilst it may be less revolutionary now, it is still great and so incredibly detailed. Be honest; you didn't know it WASN'T stop-motion until your friend told you it wasn't.</li><li>The message is truly awe inspiring and creates for a great twist! As someone who loves LEGO myself it really reminisces with me and I love it!</li></ul><br/><br/>Cons;
<ul><li>There are none (No seriously. This film is perfect).</li></ul><br/><br/>Verdict;
The LEGO Movie's own catchy song said it all; EVERYTHING IS AWESOME! From the beautiful animation, the talented cast and sweet message: what should've been a blatant toy commercial became an instant classic which is fun for the whole family.
